;; task: workspace-context-awareness
;; goal: Call workspace-state and extract the count from its first line.
;; expect: 2
;; hint: Steps to use workspace-state:
;; hint:   1. Set up source: (set-code "(define (foo x) x) (define (bar y) y)")
;; hint:   2. (workspace-state)              → returns a string:
;; hint:      "WORKSPACE: 2 defines\nDEFINE: foo\nDEFINE: bar\nMUTATIONS...\n"
;; hint:   3. The count is the first word after "WORKSPACE: " on line 1.
;; hint:   4. Use (string->list <str> "\n") to split lines (NOT string-split!)
;; hint:   5. Use (string->list <line> " ") to split words
;; hint:   6. Use (string->number <word>) to convert the count string to a number
;; hint:   7. (display <count>)
;; hint: CRITICAL: there is NO "ast:defs" or "string-split" primitive.
;; depend: edsl
